f=Brand Studio/muse/marketplace/generate-creative-ideas/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "generate-creative-ideas" (kapishdima/soundcn, 684★), fulfilling catalog's ideation-methods slot (SCAMPER, lateral thinking, constraint-based adds full situation→technique matrix, divergent/convergent split never-judge-while-generating discipline, NAF/ICE/Impact-Effort evaluation, Content Creator Mode pillars repurposing chain, research-grounded AI-creativity guards including Divergence Guard against LLM homogenization directly relevant system). NOTES SYSTEM: Muse runs GENERATION; closing phase always concept-library (dedupe score top spark register everything). two one pipeline. Content Creator Mode's pillars/repurposing chain pulse's main consumption path. Related-skills pointers (/triz, /deep-research etc.) source-repo references, local skills. RICE mention vista's skill venture altitude; it's source's evaluation table. one Thai-language note workflow source flavor output language follows operator's, system convention. --> · wf=`1. Ask       → "What problem/challenge?" \· 2. Context   → Understand current state BEFORE suggesting \· 3. Diagnose  → Match situation to technique(s) \· 4. Generate  → Walk through technique step-by-step \· 5. Evaluate  → Score and filter ideas` · wf=**Context questions (step 2):** · wf="What you currently do?", "What have you tried?", "What's working? What's not?" · wf=Anti-pattern: Jumping solutions without understanding context generic noise · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| Technique              \| One-liner                                                                          \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| ---------------------- \| ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **SCAMPER**            \| 7 lenses: Substitute, Combine, Adapt, Modify, Put to other use, Eliminate, Reverse \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **Random Word**        \| Random noun -> list attributes -> force connections to problem                     \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **Reverse Brainstorm** \| "How to make it worse?" -> Invert each idea                                        \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **First Principles**   \| Strip to fundamentals -> Rebuild from scratch                                      \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **Six Hats**           \| 6 perspectives: Facts, Feelings, Risks, Benefits, Ideas, Process                   \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **HMW**                \| Reframe as "How Might We [verb] for [user] so that [outcome]?"                     \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **Morphological Box**  \| Parameters x Variations matrix -> Combine systematically                           \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **Analogies**          \| "How does [other domain] solve this?"                                              \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **Assumptions**        \| List assumptions -> Challenge/invert each                                          \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **Forced Connections** \| Combine 2 unrelated concepts                                                       \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **Jobs to be Done**    \| "When [situation], I want [motivation], so I can [outcome]"                        \| · h3:Divergent (Generate)=\| **Oblique Strategies** \| Random creative prompts to break deadlocks                                         \| · h3:AI-Optimized (Generate + Diversify)=\| Technique                  \| One-liner                                                              \| · h3:AI-Optimized (Generate + Diversify)=\| -------------------------- \| ---------------------------------------------------------------------- \| · h3:AI-Optimized (Generate + Diversify)=\| **Incubation Cycling**     \| Generate -> Pause -> Fresh restart (no prior context) -> Compare       \| · h3:AI-Optimized (Generate + Diversify)=\| **Combinatorial Engine**   \| Abstract -> Retrieve 3 domains -> Generalize -> Combine -> Instantiate \| · h3:AI-Optimized (Generate + Diversify)=\| **Multi-Persona Parallel** \| Run 4+ personas SIMULTANEOUSLY (not sequentially)                      \| · h3:AI-Optimized (Generate + Diversify)=\| **Constraint Injection**   \| Add random constraint -> Force novel solutions                         \| · h3:AI-Optimized (Generate + Diversify)=\| **Divergence Guard**       \| Force opposite -> Domain shift -> Absurdity injection                  \| · h3:AI-Optimized (Generate + Diversify)=\| **TRIZ-AI**                \| Apply inventive principles (segmentation, nesting, dynamization, etc.) \| · h3:AI-Optimized (Generate + Diversify)=\| **Tree of Thoughts**       \| Explore multiple reasoning branches simultaneously (74% vs CoT 49%)    \| · h3:Convergent (Evaluate + Refine)=\| Technique                \| One-liner                                                        \| · h3:Convergent (Evaluate + Refine)=\| ------------------------ \| ---------------------------------------------------------------- \| · h3:Convergent (Evaluate + Refine)=\| **NAF Quick Score**      \| Rate Novelty + Attractiveness + Feasibility (1-10 each)          \| · h3:Convergent (Evaluate + Refine)=\| **Impact/Effort Matrix** \| 2x2: Quick Wins, Big Bets, Fill-ins, Avoid                       \| · h3:Convergent (Evaluate + Refine)=\| **ICE Scoring**          \| Impact x Confidence x Ease (1-10 each)                           \| · h3:Convergent (Evaluate + Refine)=\| **Idea Clustering**      \| Group similar -> Name clusters -> Pick best from each            \| · h3:Convergent (Evaluate + Refine)=\| **Dot Voting**           \| Each person gets 3-5 votes -> Surface favorites                  \| · h3:Convergent (Evaluate + Refine)=\| **Assumption Mapping**   \| Map assumptions on Importance x Certainty -> Test riskiest first \| · h2:Content Creator Mode=ideating blog posts, videos, courses, social media: · h3:Step Define Content Pillars (3-5 themes)=`Pillar = Core theme that reflects expertise + audience needs \· Example: Excel -> [Formulas, Data Viz, Automation, Tips & Tricks, Career]` · h3:Step 2: Audience-First Ideation=\| Source      \| Questions                               \| · h3:Step 2: Audience-First Ideation=\| ----------- \| --------------------------------------- \| · h3:Step 2: Audience-First Ideation=\| Pain Points \| What frustrates them most?              \| · h3:Step 2: Audience-First Ideation=\| Questions   \| What do they repeatedly ask?            \| · h3:Step 2: Audience-First Ideation=\| Gaps        \| What's poorly explained by competitors? \| · h3:Step 2: Audience-First Ideation=\| Wishes      \| What do they wish existed?              \| · h3:Step 2: Audience-First Ideation=\| Mistakes    \| What common errors do they make?        \| · h3:Step Generate Ideas (use any technique matrix)=Apply creativity techniques content pillars: · h3:Step Generate Ideas (use any technique matrix)=SCAMPER existing popular content, Reverse brainstorm: "How make worst tutorial?", Analogies: "How Netflix teach Excel?" · h3:Step Validate Before Creating=`[ ] Search demand? (keyword research) \· [ ] Real audience pain point? (comments, surveys) \· [ ] Can I add unique value? (gap analysis) \· [ ] Fits my pillars? (strategy alignment) \· [ ] Would I click this? (title/thumbnail test)` · h3:Repurposing Chain=`Blog post -> YouTube video -> Shorts/Reels -> Social posts -> Email -> Course module` · h3:Repurposing Chain=Details: content-ideation.md (source repo references/) · of:s=Use presenting ideas user: · h3:Quick List (5+ ideas)=`1. **[Idea Name]** -- [One-line description] \· 2. **[Idea Name]** -- [One-line description] \· ...` · h3:Scored List (after evaluation)=`\| # \| Idea \| N \| A \| F \| Total \| \· \|---\|------\|---\|---\|---\|-------\| \· \| 1 \| ...  \| 8 \| 9 \| 7 \| 24    \|` · h3:Concept Cards (top ideas)=Use Quick Concept Card format above top idea. · h3:Comparison Matrix (deciding between options)=`\| Criteria     \| Idea A \| Idea B \| Idea C \| \· \|-------------\|--------\|--------\|--------\| \· \| Novelty     \| 4/5    \| 3/5    \| 5/5    \| \· \| Feasibility \| 3/5    \| 5/5    \| 2/5    \| \· \| Impact      \| 5/5    \| 3/5    \| 4/5    \|` · h2:References=**Step-by-step guides**: techniques.md (source repo references/), **AI methodology research**: methodology.md (source repo references/), **Random word bank**: random-words.md (source repo references/), **Evaluation frameworks**: evaluation.md (source repo references/), **Content creator ideation**: content-ideation.md (source repo references/), **Idea development pipeline**: idea-pipeline.md (source repo references/), **AI prompt templates**: prompt-templates.md (source repo references/)